content:
✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: perfect for Coc !

Small suggestions:
- "Go evaluate" validator could handle case where remaining point becomes negative somewhere in the calculations, but at the end remaining points becomes positive - which is still "Go evaluate". There is only one test (visible for a developer) which handle that so can be hardcoded ;)
- 1337 school is a common expression in English? If not and it is a name of a specific school, I think it could be in an apostrophe
Apart from that - good job!

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: well-made puzzle

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Se résout correctement en mode rapidité

For consistency and avoiding confusion with the "eval" operation, please change all "eval points" to "evaluation points" (in all sections).

Please fix the typos:
* "poin" => "point"
* e.i => e.g.

Please change "eval" to "EVAL" and "push" to "PUSH" so that they are consistent with the cases.

The second and third paragraph basically repeat the same thing. Can they be merged be some way?

Input section
* Please add <<Line 1:>>, <<Line 2:>>, <<Next [[n]] lines:>> to the beginning of each description respectively.
* For the third description, please mention that they are strings, and operations will be either {{EVAL}} or {{PUSH}}.

Output section
* "Go evaluate" is not mentioned anywhere in the statement. Please move this requirement to the Goal section and explain what you mean by "weren't able to push at a certain operation".
* For this section, write this instead (explanation may be omitted here after it is moved to the Goal section):
<<Line 1:>> An integer for the remaining evaluation points, or a string {{Go evaluate}}.

Cases
* Tests and validators should be different.
Thanks for the good feedback, EDITED!
thanks, good suggestions i will work on them
